[2
Date: 6 Dec 2000 07:52:00 -0600
From: David Waltner-Toews <dwaltner@uoguelph.ca>

Ebola Hemorrhagic Fever: a Comment on the Case Fatality Rate
------------------------------------------------------------
I would hypothesize that the [possibly higher case fatality rate (CFR) for
nurses has something to do with dose and closeness of contact with cases.
Is there any evidence that people exposed to lower doses are able to fight
off the infection more easily? It would be interesting to stratify CFRs by
probable exposure dose.
--
David Waltner-Toews
<dwaltner@uoguelph.ca>
